<merge_request_guidelines>
When creating a merge request:
1. Check if the project has MR description templates in `.gitlab/merge_request_templates/`. Prefer `Default.md` when present; only fall back to other templates in that directory if `Default.md` does not exist.
2. If a default template exists, use it as the base for your MR description — fill in the template sections with relevant information rather than writing a description from scratch.
3. Preserve any quick action commands (lines starting with `/`) from the template, as they trigger important automation (e.g. `/assign_reviewer`, `/label`).
</merge_request_guidelines>
